The Math  class in java (part of java.lang package) provides a collection of static method to perform common mathematical operation like exponential , trignomatry, rounding etc.

1. Arithmetic operator ->
Math.abs(x)  - return the absolute value
Math.max(a, b) - return the maximum number from a and b
Math.min(a, b)
Math.sqrt(x) - return the square root of x
Math.cbrt(x) - return the cube root of x
Math.pow(x,y)
Math.hypot(a, b)


2. Rounding and truncating
Math.ceil(x)  - round up the nearest value
Math.floor(x)  - round down the nearest value
Math.round(x) - round to the nearest value( return value in int or long)


3. Trigonometry
Math.sin(x) - return sine of x (in radians)


4. Exponential and logarithmic
Math.log()  - return natural logarithm (base e) of x

5. random number
Math.random()  - return a random double between 0.0 to 1.0
for integer --> (int)(Math.random()*100) + 1;